  "title": "Question : How do you use queryParameters with url routing ?",
  "body": "Hi\r\n\r\nI created a simple widget to set the 'aroundRadius' query parameter.\r\nIt works well except when it comes to use `stateMapping` :\r\n* in stateToRoute, `aroundRadius` is missing from the argument, so I get to set it that way : \r\n```\r\n      stateToRoute: uiState => {\r\n          return {\r\n            q: uiState.query,\r\n            r: this.mainSearch.helper.state.aroundRadius //sadly, uiState.aroundRadius is undefined\r\n          };\r\n        },\r\n```\r\n* in routeToState, I'm just unable to map the http parameter back to the state : \r\n```\r\nrouteToState: routeState => {\r\n          return {\r\n            query: routeState.q,\r\n            aroundRadius: routeState.r // this does not work as when refreshing the page with the \"r\" param, the aroundRadius query param sticks set to its default value. \r\n          };\r\n        }\r\n```\r\nAs a result, I manually parse the http parameter and set the 'aroundRadius' parameter on the page initialization.\r\nWhat is the proper way to handle query parameters with url routing ?\r\nThanks \r\nThomas",
